# Commit Message Format

- Always follow this commit title format:
  - `vX.Y.Z: <concise summary>`
- Use semantic version style for the prefix (for example `v0.66.3`).
- Prefer a single-line title plus short bullet points in the body when needed.
- Keep bullets focused on user-visible behavior and important implementation details.
- Before committing, check recent commits and match this repository's style.

## Required Structure

```text
vX.Y.Z: <summary of change areas>
- <key change 1>
- <key change 2>
- <key change 3>
```

## Example

```text
v0.66.3: Analytics pagination past PostgREST limit; super-admin dashboard polish; secure analytics APIs
- Paginate PostgREST queries past 1000 rows (super-admin and shop analytics, getOrders, getProducts) via shared fetchAllRows helper
- Super-admin dashboard: total orders metric, subscription pie legend layout, theme-aware tooltips, Recharts container sizing
- Secure analytics APIs: private no-store headers, rate limits on overview and super-admin analytics, remove error detail leakage on visit/overview errors
- Client fetches use cache: no-store for analytics endpoints
```
